<ul>
<li>I will play baseball </div></li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<p>The important part isn&#8217;t to learn the new words (on the left side), but to make sure you know the verbs, as well as how to do each conjugation. Go ahead and move on to the worksheet, where you&#8217;ll be getting more practice with conjugating verbs.</p>
<p><strong>Extra Content:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="../../wp-content/uploads/2010/01/conjugating-verbs.pdf">Conjugating Verbs Worksheet</a></li>
<li><a href="../../wp-content/uploads/2010/01/verb-particles-practice.pdf">Verb / Particles practice Worksheet</a></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Before You Move On:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Know how to use 〜ます</li>
<li>Know how to use 〜ました</li>
<li>Know how to use 〜ません</li>
<li>Know how to use 〜ませんでした</li>
<li>Know how to pronounce them all properly (especially ました and ませんでした)</li>
<li>Have an &#8220;80%&#8221; knowledge of the common verbs list.</li>
<li>Feel moderately comfortable with the particles を and に in terms of how / when they are used.</li>
</ul>
